<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2009-04-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Biologic Vaccines: A Panacea For Infectious Diseases?</TITLE><BODY>The threat of new disease pandemics has spurred the development of biologic vaccines, which promise tremendous improvements in global and local health. Several lend themselves to the prevention or treatment of chronic diseases. But the uncertainties of whom to vaccinate raise the question of whether the health care system can make these promising products viable.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>